# Mouse Coordinates Tracker

Mouse Coordinates Tracker is a simple Python program that displays the current position of the mouse cursor on the screen.

## What it does

This program continuously monitors the position of the mouse cursor on the screen and displays its coordinates in real-time. It provides a convenient way to track the mouse's location, which can be useful for various purposes such as software development, graphic design, and user interface testing.

## How to use

1. Run the program by executing the `mouse_tracker.py` script.

2. Press Ctrl + Alt keys simultaneously to capture the mouse coordinates.

3. The coordinates will be displayed in a graphical user interface (GUI) window.

4. Move the mouse cursor around the screen to see the coordinates update in real-time.

5. Press the Esc key to exit the program.

## Customization

The program can be easily customized to fit your specific needs. You can modify the code to perform additional actions when certain conditions are met, such as saving the coordinates to a file or triggering other events based on the mouse position.

